a 1258–1321","1258–1321":"1258–1321","1272–1295":"1272–1295","1288–1328":"1288–1328","–1295":"–1295","1230–Female":"1230–Overleden","BEF 1295":"vóór 1295","1258":"1258","1321":"1321","1288":"1288","1230":"1230","Abt 1258":"circa 1258","Cir 1288":"1288","1295":"1295","1272":"1272","before 28 September 1295":"vóór 28 september 1295","1328":"1328","Sapcote, Leic, Engl":"Sapcote, Leicestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Sapcote, Leicestershire, England":"Sapcote, Leicestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1258–1321":"about 1258–1321","1258–1321":"1258–1321","1272–1295":"1272–1295","1288–1328":"1288–1328","–1295":"–1295","1230–Female":"1230–Deceased","BEF 1295":"before 1295","1258":"1258","1321":"1321","1288":"1288","1230":"1230","Abt 1258":"about 1258","Cir 1288":"1288","1295":"1295","1272":"1272","before 28 September 1295":"before 28 September 1295","1328":"1328","Sapcote, Leic, Engl":"Sapcote, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Sapcote, Leicestershire, England":"Sapcote, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Basset","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: from a diminutive of Old French <i>bas(se)</i> ‘short, of low stature’ (see   Bas  ).","English: variant of   Bassett  , a cognate of 1 above.","In some cases also an altered form of French <b>Besset</b> (see   Bessette   2). Compare   Bassette   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Bas","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Mauricio, Abelardo, Florencio, Francisco, Jorge, Luis, Manuel, Pedro, Soledad, Vicente.  Eastern Slavic Dmytro, Liya, Pyotr, Sergey.","Catalan: habitational name from a place so named in the district of La Garrotxa, Catalonia.","Basque: topographic name for someone who lived by a wood, from <i>baso</i> ‘wood, forest’."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Basset was born about 1258, in Sapcote, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Simon Basset of Sapcote and Mrs. Simon Bassett. He had at least 1 son with Elizabeth de Coleville. He died in 1321, at the age of 64."},"et":{"Abt 1258–1321":"umbes 1258–1321","1258–1321":"1258–1321","1272–1295":"1272–1295","1288–1328":"1288–1328","–1295":"–1295","1230–Female":"1230–Surnud","BEF 1295":"enne 1295","1258":"1258","1321":"1321","1288":"1288","1230":"1230","Abt 1258":"umbes 1258","Cir 1288":"1288","1295":"1295","1272":"1272","before 28 September 1295":"enne 28. septembrit 1295","1328":"1328","Sapcote, Leic, Engl":"Sapcote, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sapcote, Leicestershire, England":"Sapcote, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1258–1321":"noin 1258–1321","1258–1321":"1258–1321","1272–1295":"1272–1295","1288–1328":"1288–1328","–1295":"–1295","1230–Female":"1230–Kuollut","BEF 1295":"ennen vuotta 1295","1258":"1258","1321":"1321","1288":"1288","1230":"1230","Abt 1258":"noin 1258","Cir 1288":"1288","1295":"1295","1272":"1272","before 28 September 1295":"en